Vice President Yemi Osibanjo yesterday called on Christians to fast and pray for the Saturday’s general elections to be peaceful. Osinbajo was speaking in Jos, the Plateau State capital, yesterday at the Day of Prayer for 2019 General Elections organised by the Christian Association of Nigeria. He said the destiny of the pastors has a crucial role in the destiny of the nation. The vice president commended Governor  Simon Lalong for ensuring peace in Plateau State. Helicopter crash: CAN felicitates Osinbajo Helicopter crash: How we survived – Osinbajo Happening Now: Osinbajo in thanksgiving service after helicopter crash